The paper deals with learning in a passive setting, which is a subfield of machine learning. The use of prior knowledge to explicitly utilize the target risk in the learning process suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of "Learning Theory" (cs.LG). The analysis of sample complexity and the use of stochastic optimization algorithm suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of "Information Theory" (cs.IT), "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI), "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS), and "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI).
